tissueExpression.summary: Normal tissues showed moderate cytoplasmic staining. Trophoblastic cells and a subset of lymphoid cells displayed strong positivity while fallopian tube exhibited strong membranous staining. Liver, skeletal myocytes and the glial cells were weakly stained or negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Low consistency between antibody staining and RNA expression data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human fallopian tube shows membranous positivity in glandular cells.

tissueExpression.summary: Malignant cells showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic staining. Several cases of malignant lymphomas and testicular cancers were negative.
